author: Steve Vivian
title: No new NT coronavirus cases in over a week, but 'complacency' could be biggest threat says Health Minister
description: The NT has not recorded any new coronavirus cases since April 6, but restrictions including social-distancing measures will remain in place, as the NT Health Minister warns the virus could yet be "let loose" in the Territory.
content:
Updated 
April 14, 2020 12:25:31
The Northern Territory has not recorded any new cases of COVID-19 for over a week, but the NT Health Minister says it is "too early to talk about lifting restrictions".
